reviews.text: We are visiting Kiev and where looking for a place near by to eat. And let me tell you this,  the BEST FOOD you can find locally!!! The salads, the fish soup the sandwich with beef the wings, please don't go anywhere else! This is the best place with fresh food and amazing service! We are definitely coming back!!

Celebrated Christmas at Tatarin's with a big family (20 people)!!! Thanks to the administrator Inna and Maryana for the service.
We had a wonderful rest in the "On the Fisherman" cabin with a fireplace. Warm, plenty of space. The cuisine is delicious, the portions are large, and we took a lot home. Marinated shish kebab.
Chebureks - special thanks to the chefs - an incredible pleasure. Delicious, real.
The children had pizza - they liked it.
The service is excellent.

We ordered a banquet for our son's christening on 07.10.2023, we ordered two months in advance and agreed on everything, Natalya told us something about the renovation all this time, communication was easy, we chose the menu very quickly, we ordered a children's table separately, Natalya advised us a very cool host (we very satisfied) for 22 people + children's table and service fee, we got 27,500, we also ordered 3 rooms for our guests for 750 hryvnias per one. We were sure that everything would be at the highest level because we love the second establishment of the same owners. Our long-awaited day of celebration came, we arrived at the restaurant, and here the number one surprise awaited us in the nearby memorial hall (no one warned us, even though we were there in the evening setting up a photo booth and bringing in water with fruit) our hall was booked for 1:30 p.m. by our host he tells us that he cannot conduct anything until 3:00 p.m. because there is a wake, the table is not set at all, although we asked that everything be already on the tables and discussed everything in detail, they completely forgot about the children's table, we had to run after them and ask them to set the table and they put a children's table for which we actually paid, the room itself is damp, there is a huge crack on the wall, there was no one to repair it, I don't understand at all why it was necessary to talk about it, the food is delicious, the guests all liked it (but this is the only thing that pleased us), the staff is unpleasant , were rude and rarely appeared in the hall, most of the time I had to run after them. Natalia herself turned from a pleasant woman with whom we talked when we ordered all this into an unpleasant woman, there was 0 support from her during our holiday. Our holiday is over, we asked if we can pick up the food in the morning, we were told that yes, we ordered a lot so that our guests were not hungry, so there was not enough left, we came in the morning at 8:30 and saw a shocking picture, the girls were celebrating something, many empty bottles of beef and someone's sneakers, they only gave us a cake and said that we had nothing left!!! We will not go there or to any of their institutions again!!!!
P.S. be prepared that even if you don't take it home, you will have to disassemble and throw it away yourself (but don't worry, they will give you a knife to shovel all the balls and a broom to clean up all that and the monsoon bag, I was very happy while I was cleaning the hall))) this is probably in the amount for the service was not included)

Dear restaurant owners! Please note that 2 residential complexes have already appeared near your restaurant in recent years, in which people live. Loud music that you turn on at the summer playground prevents the residents of these buildings from resting. Several laws prohibit loud music outdoors at any time, not just at night.

1. The military administration of the Buchansky district banned concerts, karaoke, and discos after 9 p.m. Order of the Chief of the Buchansk District Military Administration dated 06.06.2023 No. 28/vs

2. Article 24 of the Law of Ukraine "On Ensuring Sanitary and Epidemic Welfare of the Population" states that it is not allowed to make noise near residential buildings. There is an order of the Ministry of Health, which states that even during the day, the noise level near residential buildings should not exceed 55 dB (this is the level of loud conversation), not loud music. Article 182 of the Code of Ukraine on Administrative Offenses stipulates the maximum penalty for violation of the provisions of this Law - confiscation of musical equipment (for repeated offenses).

A request to the restaurant owners. Consider that people in their own apartments need to rest, not listen to your loud music. Especially on weekends and in the evening and at night. If necessary, we will be forced to call the police and demand compliance with the requirements of the law to ensure our own peace of mind. You have a room where you can hold loud events and not disturb anyone.
